verbose_text: While different cytokines have already been explored in fish, data on potential interactions with the GH/IGF-I axis are still very fragmentary and mainly deal with TNF-alpha : e.g., in GH injected tilapia, TNF-alpha expression was elevated in the liver [XREF_BIBR] and in a GH-RH-treated flounder embryonic cell line, TNF-alpha mRNA was also induced, while in a primary pituitary cell culture, TNF-alpha mRNA was decreased [XREF_BIBR].
